  "prompt": "Who are some of the famous programmers from India?",
  "response": "India has produced several renowned programmers who have made significant contributions to the field of computer science and technology. Here are a few notable names:\n\n1. **Sundar Pichai** - CEO of Alphabet Inc. and its subsidiary Google LLC. Pichai has a background in technology and engineering, having worked on various products at Google including Chrome and Android.\n\n2. **Satya Nadella** - CEO of Microsoft. Nadella, though primarily known for his executive role, has a strong background in engineering and has led numerous projects at Microsoft, notably in cloud computing and AI.\n\n3. **Nandan Nilekani** - Co-founder of Infosys, a multinational corporation that provides business consulting, information technology, and outsourcing services. Although he is known more for his role as an entrepreneur, he has a programming background.\n\n4. **Ruchi Sanghvi** - One of the first female engineers at Facebook. She played a key role in developing Facebook\u2019s News Feed feature. She later went on to co-found Cove, which was acquired by Dropbox.\n\n5. **Arvind Krishna** - CEO of IBM, known for leading IBM's cloud and cognitive software division. He has a deep background in technology and computer engineering.\n\n6. **Srivatsan Rajan** - Former Chairman of Bain & Company India, although not known primarily as a programmer, has a robust background in computer science and engineering.\n\n7. **Shantanu Narayen** - CEO of Adobe Systems. He has a background in computer science and played a key role in transforming Adobe into a leader in digital media and marketing software.\n\nThese individuals have not only contributed through their programming skills but also played significant roles in leading, innovating, and shaping the tech industry globally.",
